[2] [P-Observations-N] | Value is an estimate. Details of the estimation not available
[3] [P-Observations-N] | Value is an estimate. Details of the estimation not available

[4] [P-Observations-N] | 27.1% for river recharge, 27% for Landscaping, 21.8% for defrosting the road, 8.6% for agricultural irrigation, 8% for production/service, 3.8% for toilet use, 2.4% for entertainment use, 0.8% for industrial use, 0.4% for cooling the road.
[5] [P-Observations-N] | 3.208 billion m3 from the cities and 0.324 billion from the towns.
[6] [P-Reference Area-N] | There is no wastewater treatment in Ethiopia.
[7] [P-Observations-S] | Direct use in 2012 consists of 20 289 511.06m3 from domestic origin and 10 019 591.1m3 from industrial origin.
[8] [P-Observations-S] | Reuse activity: Irrigation of crops, parks, gardens, reforestation (59.68%), dust control (22.58%), irrigation and dust control (14.52%), industry (3.23%).
[9] [P-Reference Area-S] | Data available for the case of the St. Kitts Marriott Hotel: Irrigation of it's golf course with 236 396.68 m3/year (year 2011)
